The paper deals with learning efficient representation for handwritten word images using deep convolutional neural networks. This falls under the computer vision (cs.CV) and information retrieval (cs.IR) sub-categories. The paper also discusses the use of synthetic data and fine-tuning techniques, which are common in machine learning (cs.LG) and natural language processing (cs.CL) sub-categories. Additionally, the paper uses visualization techniques to analyze the learned in-variances, which is a common topic in artificial intelligence (cs.AI) sub-category.
